<title>JAPAN: 'Tankan' shows Japan firms see spending up 6.6 pct.</title>
<headline>'Tankan' shows Japan firms see spending up 6.6 pct.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-08-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Major Japanese companies plan a 6.6 percent increase in capital investment in fiscal 1996/97, ending next March 31, following a 1.2 percent rise in the previous year, the Bank of Japan (BOJ) said in its August &quot;tankan&quot; short-term corporate survey released on Wednesday.</p>
<p>FORECASTS FOR CHANGES IN CAPITAL SPENDING (1996/97)</p>
<p>						  latest     prev  1995/96</p>
<p>						 forecast  forecast actual</p>
<p> Major firms				   +6.6     +6.0     +1.2</p>
<p>    Manufacturers			    +7.6     +6.7     +7.8</p>
<p>    Non-manufacturers			+6.2     +5.7     -1.6</p>
